The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Rickshaw puller gets cash reward
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Rickshaw puller gets cash reward
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                                        Mohammed Salim    
	New Delhi, Sept. 21: Delhi police today announced a cash reward of Rs 25,000 for the rickshaw puller who threw a brick towards two motorcycle-borne gunmen outside Jama Masjid on Sunday morning.         
	Mohammed Salims action possibly saved other tourists because the duo fled when the brick was hurled at them. When the bike sped away, Salim and a police constable chased the attackers.         
	We have announced a cash reward of Rs 25,000 for Salim, said Rajan Bhagat, Delhi police spokesperson. The police will provide him security and recommend his name for a gallantry award.         
	The 26-year-old is happy and scared. I am scared. Who will look after my family if they kill me? he asked.         
	Two in mail net        
	Two persons were caught on Monday in Mumbai in connection with the terror email that surfaced after the Jama Masjid shooting.                                                                                                                                                          
